^ "List of Players under Written Contract Registered Between 01/07/2010 and 31/07/2010".

people.name: Shane Cansdell-Sherriff
people.aboutText: Marko Tomasović (born November 10, 1981) is a Croatian Boxer and Kickboxer, best known to qualify for the Olympics 2008 at super heavyweight.

people.name: Chris Canty
people.aboutText: Christopher Lee Canty (born November 10, 1982) is an American football defensive end for the Baltimore Ravens of the National Football League (NFL). He was drafted by the Dallas Cowboys in the fourth round of the 2005 NFL Draft. He has also played for the New York Giants, winning Super Bowl XLVI with them in 2011.

people.name: Clayton Fortune
people.aboutText:
Clayton Alexander Fortune (born 10 November 1982) is an English football defender who plays for Conference South side Weston-super-Mare.
He spent the first six years of his career at Bristol City, between 2001 and 2006. He then began a two-year spell with Leyton Orient, before signing with Darlington in summer 2008.

people.name: Heather Matarazzo
people.aboutText: Heather Christina Marie Matarazzo (born November 10, 1982) is an American actress. Her breakthrough role was as a geeky girl in the film Welcome to the Dollhouse (1995). She played Lilly in The Princess Diaries (2001) and The Princess Diaries 2: Royal Engagement (2004).

people.name: Matt Pagnozzi
people.aboutText: Matthew Thomas Pagnozzi (born November 10, 1982) is an American professional baseball catcherwho is a free agent. He has also played for the St. Louis Cardinals, Colorado Rockies, Pittsburgh Pirates, Houston Astros, and Milwaukee Brewers.

people.name: Rafael Rosell
people.aboutText: Rafael Rosell IV (born November 10, 1982) is a Filipino actor and model. Rosell is best known for playing Brandon Brazil on the ABS-CBN romance drama Midnight Phantom, Marco De Silva in Kristine, and as Mayor Edson Zaguirre in Dahil Sa Pag-ibig. A known talent of ABS-CBN for several years, Rosell is now under contract with GMA Network.

people.name: Ahmet Kural
people.aboutText: Ahmet Kural (born 10 November 1982, in Kütahya) is a Turkish actor.

people.name: Brian Dinkelman
people.aboutText: Brian Adam Dinkelman (born November 10, 1983) is an American retired professional baseball second baseman. Dinkelman was born on November 10, 1983, in Centralia, Illinois. After graduating from Centralia High School in 2002, Dinkelman attended McKendree University and graduated in 2006; he was later drafted by the Minnesota Twins in the eighth round of the 2006 MLB draft.

people.name: Dinko Felić
people.aboutText:
Dinko Felić (born 10 November 1983) is a Bosnian-born Norwegian footballer who plays for Syrianska FC as a forward.
Felić was born in Bosnia but his family relocated to Norway when he was twelve and settled down in Vågå. In 1999 he moved to Kongsvinger to attend a school which focused on football.

people.name: Miranda Lambert
people.aboutText: Miranda Leigh Lambert (born November 10, 1983) is an American country music singer and songwriter who gained fame as a finalist on the 2003 season of Nashville Star, where she finished in third place and later signed to Epic Records. Lambert made her debut with the release of "Me and Charlie Talking", the first single from her 2005 debut album Kerosene. This album, which was certified Platinum in the United States, also produced the singles "Bring Me Down", "Kerosene", and "New Strings".

people.name: Ryan Mattheus
people.aboutText: Ryan Arthur Mattheus (born November 10, 1983) is an American professional baseball pitcher in the Cincinnati Reds organzation. He has played in Major League Baseball (MLB) for the Washington Nationals and Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim. He is a sinkerballer.

people.name: Craig Smith
people.aboutText: Craig Smith (born November 10, 1983) is an American professional basketball player. He recently played for Ironi Nes Ziona of the Israeli Basketball Premier League.

people.name: Marius Žaliūkas
people.aboutText: Marius Žaliūkas (born 10 November 1983 in Kaunas, Lithuanian SSR) is a Lithuanian footballer who last played for Scottish Championship club Rangers. He plays as a centre back, but can also play as a defensive midfielder. Žaliūkas has previously played for Inkaras Kaunas, FBK Kaunas, FK Šilutė, Hearts and Leeds United.

people.name: Britt Irvin
people.aboutText: Jean-Martial Kipre (born 10 November 1984 in Adjamé) is an Ivorian football (soccer) player who currently plays for SC Toulon.

people.name: Jean-Martial Kipré
people.aboutText: Brittney Elizabeth "Britt" Irvin (born November 10, 1984) is a Canadian actress and singer, as well as a regular voice actor for Ocean Productions. She is typically credited as Britt Irvin in works since 2003, and as Brittney Irvin in works prior to 2003, though exceptions exist both ways. Britt is best known for playing Katie in Scary Godmother: Halloween Spooktacular and its sequel Scary Godmother: The Revenge of Jimmy.

people.name: Jarno Mattila
people.aboutText: Ludovic Joseph Obraniak (Polish pronunciation: [luˈdɔvʲik ɔˈbraɲak]; born 10 November 1984) is a French-born Polish footballer who plays for Israeli Premier League club Maccabi Haifa and the Poland national football team.

people.name: Ludovic Obraniak
people.aboutText:
Jarno Mattila is a Finnish professional footballer who currently plays for the Veikkausliiga side FC Haka in Finland. He usually plays on the left side as a defender or a midfielder, originally he has mostly played at striker.
He won the Finnish Cup with his side FC Haka in 2005.

people.name: Kendrick Perkins
people.aboutText: Kendrick La'Dale Perkins (born November 10, 1984) is an American professional basketball player for the New Orleans Pelicans of the National Basketball Association (NBA).

people.name: Dannic
people.aboutText:
Daan Romers (born 10 November 1985), better known by his stage name Dannic, is a Dutch progressive house DJ and producer. He is known for his work in collaborations with Hardwell, Dyro, Sick Individuals, and publishes his music through the record label Revealed Recordings.
As of 2013, he has a radio show called Front of House.

people.name: Ricki-Lee Coulter
people.aboutText: Ricki-Lee Dawn Coulter (born 10 November 1985), also known mononymously as Ricki-Lee, is an Australian singer, songwriter, television and radio presenter. She was born in Auckland, New Zealand, grew up on the Gold Coast, Queensland and began performing at the age of 15. In 2004, she auditioned for the second season of Australian Idol and placed seventh in the finals round.

people.name: Daan Huiskamp
people.aboutText:
Daan Huiskamp (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈdaːn ˈɦœy̯skɐɱp]; born November 10, 1985 in Eerbeek, Brummen, Gelderland) is a Dutch footballer. He currently plays with DVS '33.
He first played in several youth clubs, first Eerbekse Boys, second SBV Vitesse and lastly FC Utrecht.

people.name: Aleksandar Kolarov
people.aboutText:
Cherno Samba (born 10 November 1985) is a former professional footballer who played as a forward.
He represented England at every youth level up to the under-20 team, having moved to England at an early age. He earned his first full cap for Gambia in 2008.

people.name: Cherno Samba
people.aboutText: Aleksandar Kolarov (Serbian Cyrillic: Александар Коларов; Serbian pronunciation: [alɛksǎːndar kɔlǎrɔʋ]; born 10 November 1985) is a Serbian professional footballer who plays for English club Manchester City and the Serbia national team. Although primarily a left back, Kolarov can also operate anywhere along the left flank and is known for his overlapping runs on the wing and his ball striking ability. He was named Serbian Player of the Year in 2011.

people.name: Giovonnie Samuels
people.aboutText: Giovonnie Lavette Samuels (born November 10, 1985) is an American actress best known for her role as Nia Moseby in The Suite Life of Zack & Cody and for being a series regular on All That.

people.name: Krystian Trochowski
people.aboutText:
Krystian Trochowski (born 10 November 1985) is a retired German international rugby union player, formerly playing for the Berliner RC in the Rugby-Bundesliga and the German national rugby union team.
He has played rugby since 1999.
His last game for Germany was a friendly against Switzerland on 29 September 2007.

people.name: Aaron Crow
people.aboutText: Aaron James Crow (born November 10, 1986) is an American professional baseball pitcher who is a free agent.

people.name: Will Hendry
people.aboutText: William Michael "Will" Hendry (born 10 November 1986 in Maidenhead, Berkshire, England) is an English footballer playing as a midfielder for Hayes & Yeading.

people.name: Ilias Iliadis
people.aboutText:
Ilias Iliadis (Greek: Ηλίας Ηλιάδης, born Jarji Zviadauri, Georgian: ჯარჯი ზვიადაური, on 10 November 1986) is a Georgian-born Greek judoka who has been competing for Greece since the start of his international career.
He won a gold medal in the half-middleweight (81 kg) division at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens at age 17. Illiadis also won a gold medal 6 years later at the 2010 World Judo Championships in Tokyo in the −90 kg category.

people.name: Goran Jerković
people.aboutText: Goran Jerković (born 10 November 1986) is a French footballer playing with Jagodina.

people.name: Stanislav Namașco
people.aboutText: Joshua Michael "Josh" Peck (born November 10, 1986) is an American actor. He is best known for playing Josh Nichols in the Nickelodeon live-action sitcom Drake & Josh. He began his career as a child actor in the late 1990s and early 2000s, and became known to young audiences after his role on The Amanda Show.

people.name: Josh Peck
people.aboutText: Stanislav Namaşco (born 10 November 1986 in Tiraspol) is a Moldovan footballer, who plays for AZAL PFC.

people.name: Eric Thames
people.aboutText: Samuel Kamau Wanjiru (10 November 1986 – 15 May 2011) was a Kenyan athlete who specialised in long distance running. He became a professional at a young age and broke the world record in the half marathon when he was 18 years old. In 2007, he broke the 20 km road running record and improved the half marathon record by over twenty seconds.

people.name: Samuel Wanjiru
people.aboutText: Eric Allyn Thames (pronounced /θeɪms/) (born November 10, 1986) is an American professional baseball infielder for the NC Dinos of the KBO League. He was previously an outfielder in Major League Baseball (MLB) for the Toronto Blue Jays and Seattle Mariners.

people.name: Britney Amber
people.aboutText:
Edi Maia (born 10 November 1987 in Setúbal) is a Portuguese pole vaulter. He competed in the pole vault event at the 2012 Summer Olympics.
His outdoor personal best in the event is 5.70 metres achieved in Lisbon in 2013.

people.name: Edi Maia
people.aboutText: Britney Amber (born November 10, 1986) is an American pornographic actress.

people.name: Sam Malsom
people.aboutText: Samuel Andrew "Sam" Malsom (born 10 November 1987) is an English professional footballer who plays for Nikos & Sokratis Erimis in Cyprus where he plays as a winger, attacking midfielder or forward.

people.aboutText: Theo "Teddy" Peckham (born November 10, 1987) is a Canadian professional ice hockey defenceman who is currently playing for the Wichita Thunder of the ECHL. He is the half-brother of Angela James - one of the first female hockey players to be inducted into the Hockey Hall of Fame.

people.name: Theo Peckham
people.aboutText:
Kana Lais Oya (born November 10, 1987, in Shizuoka Prefecture, Japan), simply known as Kana Oya (大屋 夏南, Ōya Kana), is a Japanese model who is represented by the talent agency, LDH. She was raised in Brazil.
